Description: The Three Virtues; Charity, Faith and Hope; a young woman (Caritas) seated on clouds and suckling a baby at left; a putto holding a cross (Fides) and looking on at centre; a third putto (Spes) holding an anchor at right. c.1593 Etching
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (3)
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Charles Francis Arnold Howard, 5th Earl of Wicklow
